narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This class was perhaps one of the most interesting and conceptually challenging courses of my life. It introduced me to place based scholarship and new approaches to reading and interpreting literature, culture and film.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: reasonable and very interesting readings, inclusion of understudied writers and cultures, well-organized class discussions, helpful writing and presentation assignments No weaknesses!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! This course is not just interesting in terms of subject matter but also because of Professor Bozovic's teaching style. Everyone should take this course to experience a different way of reading and understanding space and cultural productions.
